{{for|the Amazonian tree|Dipteryx odorata}} [[File:PE-mapa-Cumaru.png|thumb|right|230px|Location of Cumaru within Pernambuco.]] [[File:Cumaru-Igreja-Matriz.jpg|thumb|Cumaru main Church]] '''Cumaru''' is a city in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. It is 132&nbsp;km away from the state capital [[Recife]], and has an estimated ([[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|Ibge 2009]]) population of 13.812 inhabitants.
==Geography== [[File:Cumaru-Zona-rural.jpg|thumb|right|230px|Rural area view of Cumaru]] * State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Agreste|Agreste Pernambucano]] * Boundaries - [[Surubim]] ('''N'''); [[Bezerros]] ('''S'''); [[Passira]] ('''E'''); [[Riacho das Almas]] ('''W'''). * Area - 292.24&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 443 m * Hidrography - [[Capibaribe River]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[hipoxer√≥fila]] * Clima - [[Semi arid]] hot * Annual average temperature - 25.0 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 132&nbsp;km
==Economy== [[File:Cumaru-Hotel-Municipal.jpg|thumb|right|230px|Municipal Hotel]] The main economic activities in '''Cumaru''' are based in [[agribusiness]], especially [[beans]], [[maize|corn]]; and [[livestock]] such as [[cattle]], [[sheep]], [[goats]], [[pigs]] and [[poultry]].
